Modifications
================================================================================

  Modified by Rennsou1_2006 (2026)

  Changes to the original mitsuman/mdx2wav:
    - 64-bit (MinGW64) compilation support (pointer truncation fix)
    - YMFM YM2151 emulation engine integration
    - Replaced fmgen with Nuked OPM (cycle-accurate YM2151 emulator)
    - PCM8A / PCM8PP driver auto-detection via MDX pre-scan
    - Variable frequency PCM support (MXDRVp — developed by Rennsou1_2006 for PCM8PP)
    - MAME-accurate ADPCM decoding (diff_lookup + index_shift)
    - 16-bit / 8-bit PCM playback support (PCM8PP extended modes)
    - OPM/PCM volume balancing (referenced from MDXWin)
    - ReplayGain peak normalization (two-pass rendering)
    - JSON metadata extraction (-i flag: driver type, BPM, duration)
    - Native 62500Hz output (no resampling)
    - Windows binary mode stdout fix
    - MXDRV original bug fixes (referenced from MDXWin):
        KeyOn delay gap, sync signal 1-tick offset,
        hardware LFO phase offset
